01:17.920 --> 01:19.921
Ryker, I'm in.

01:19.955 --> 01:21.255
How many?

01:21.290 --> 01:22.457
I count 11.

01:22.491 --> 01:23.924
Copy that.

01:23.942 --> 01:26.761
On my word, take them out,

01:26.795 --> 01:27.962
all of them.

01:31.867 --> 01:34.002
The men in that room
just slaughtered

01:34.036 --> 01:35.570
the couple that lived
in this house.

01:35.604 --> 01:37.655
Give them the opportunity,
they'll kill you, too.

01:40.175 --> 01:41.509
Now move.

02:11.323 --> 02:14.308
♪

02:14.326 --> 02:15.476
Next?

02:15.511 --> 02:17.478
Double doors, three o'clock.

02:17.513 --> 02:18.813
The package is inside.

02:31.093 --> 02:33.561
Ryker, th-the package...

02:33.595 --> 02:35.129
The baby is the package.

02:35.164 --> 02:37.031
Grab it and get out of there.

02:37.066 --> 02:39.133
But what am,
what am I supposed...?

02:39.168 --> 02:40.301
Move, Walker.

02:40.335 --> 02:41.969
I'm your handler
and that's an order.

02:58.036 --> 02:59.754
Oh, my God, he knows.

03:03.625 --> 03:05.660
Hey, honey.

03:05.694 --> 03:07.545
You ready for
my big surprise?

03:07.579 --> 03:09.247
Absolutely.

03:09.298 --> 03:11.866
You know how much
I love surprises.

03:11.900 --> 03:13.468
Chuck, where are we?

03:13.502 --> 03:14.702
Okay, here we
go, up farther.

03:14.737 --> 03:16.704
Straight, straight,
straight, straight,

03:16.722 --> 03:18.406
and ta-dah!

03:20.976 --> 03:23.077
Oh, my God,
this is the house.

03:23.112 --> 03:24.846
It's our house.

03:24.880 --> 03:26.047
How, how did
you do th...?

03:26.081 --> 03:27.248
The real estate
agent gave me

03:27.282 --> 03:30.184
the keys so we could try
it out for the weekend.

03:30.219 --> 03:31.419
Um, full disclosure--

03:31.453 --> 03:33.955
I think she might have a
little crush on me, so...

03:33.989 --> 03:35.757
Chuck, this is,
this is beautiful,

03:35.791 --> 03:37.525
but we still
can't afford it.

03:37.559 --> 03:38.793
Actually, we can.

03:38.827 --> 03:40.294
I was talking
to Beckman, and

03:40.329 --> 03:42.396
apparently her offer
to rejoin the CIA

03:42.431 --> 03:43.798
comes with a
signing bonus,

03:43.832 --> 03:45.767
which is enough for a
down payment on the house

03:45.801 --> 03:48.369
and that dresser I've been
eyeing at Anthropologie.

03:48.403 --> 03:51.806
Uh, I don't know
what to say.

03:51.840 --> 03:53.207
Don't say anything.

03:53.242 --> 03:54.375
Just visualize.

03:54.409 --> 03:55.810
Think to yourself,

03:55.844 --> 03:58.079
"What would my life be like
in such an amazing home

03:58.113 --> 04:00.882
with the most dashing
man I've ever met?"

04:00.916 --> 04:02.049
Okay.

04:02.084 --> 04:03.217
All right,
all right, so

04:03.252 --> 04:05.419
after a hard day's
work, we come home

04:05.437 --> 04:07.455
to the sweet, sweet
sounds of Nina Simone

04:07.489 --> 04:09.857
emanating
from our record player,

04:09.892 --> 04:11.292
which would fit perfectly--
I don't know--

04:11.326 --> 04:12.827
say, in this corner
right behind me.

04:12.861 --> 04:13.895
Huh?

04:13.929 --> 04:15.296
Open floor plan--
great for relaxing

04:15.330 --> 04:17.298
and watching your
husband cook.

04:17.332 --> 04:19.065
Cooking and talking,
talking and cooking.

04:19.101 --> 04:22.637
This area right here--
perfect for my game chairs.

04:22.671 --> 04:24.472
Or not.

04:24.506 --> 04:26.774
Maybe we'll talk
about that, but this,

04:26.809 --> 04:28.843
this is perfect.

04:28.877 --> 04:30.945
The door frame?

04:31.980 --> 04:34.315
When Ellie and I
were kids,

04:34.349 --> 04:36.284
our dad would measure us
every year

04:36.318 --> 04:37.351
to see how tall
we were getting.

04:37.386 --> 04:39.020
I remember being
so excited

04:39.054 --> 04:40.822
when I was finally
taller than Ellie.

04:40.856 --> 04:42.456
It took a while, but

04:42.491 --> 04:44.492
tenth grade was
a good year for me.

04:47.830 --> 04:49.463
What's the matter, what's
the matter, what have I done?

04:49.481 --> 04:51.132
Something-Something's missing,
something's wrong?

04:51.166 --> 04:52.767
Is it the game chairs?
'Cause those are negotiable.

04:52.801 --> 04:54.001
No, Chuck,
it's not that.

04:54.036 --> 04:56.804
Um, look, I
want this house

04:56.839 --> 04:58.940
and I want the life that
you have envisioned for us.

04:58.974 --> 05:01.976
I want every
single part of it.

05:02.010 --> 05:04.679
It's just that something urgent
has come up.

05:04.713 --> 05:05.680
What is it?

05:05.714 --> 05:07.148
You know you can tell me
anything.

05:09.051 --> 05:11.052
Well, that's just it.

05:12.287 --> 05:14.222
This time, Chuck,
I can't tell you.

05:22.197 --> 05:24.332
There are more men coming.

05:24.366 --> 05:25.566
Get the package
and get out of there.

05:30.372 --> 05:32.223
It's going to be okay.

